;
; This script is a small Dark Elven outpost to be loaded when Mardhrel characters
; want to hold a meeting, etc.
;
; REGION 206 DEFINITIONS
REGIONDEF 206 SEASONS
REGIONDEF 206 TIME
REGIONDEF 206 WINTERTEMP 1
REGIONDEF 206 SUMMERTEMP 60
REGIONDEF 206 SPRINGTEMP 35
REGIONDEF 206 AUTUMNTEMP 35
REGIONDEF 206 TELEPORT DISALLOWED
REGIONDEF 206 SUMMONING ALLOWED
REGIONDEF 206 DEPART DISALLOWED
VARIABLE MEANTIME
;
MACRO 19
IFPREVERB RETREAT -1
   IFVAR MONINROOM > PLRSINROOM
      SKILLCHECK 10 -10 DUMMY1
      IFVAR DISGUISED = 1
         SPELL 250
         EQUAL DUMMY1 1
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY1 >= 0
      ELSE
         CLEARVERB
         ECHO PLAYER You try and retreat, but there are too many attackers.
         ECHO OTHERS %N tries frantically to get away from %h attackers, almost to the point of flailing.
         EQUAL ROUNDTIME 2
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
   IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 0
      IFVAR DISGUISED = 1
         IFVAR MONINROOM > 1
            ECHO ALL Sensing a hidden presence, your foe searches by normal and arcane means.
            SPELL 250
            ECHO PLAYER You have been discovered!
            ECHO OTHERS %N has been discovered!
         ENDIF
      ENDIF
   ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 3370
NAME Entry Hall
REGION 206
DEEPCAVE
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CHANNEL 76
CALL 33
CALL 19
*DESCRIPTION_START
Rough, unfinished rock forms the four walls of this large rectangular room.
Globes of magelight are placed at regular intervals, hovering silently above
blackened silver sconces cast in the shape of sleek firedrakes with their
jaws agape. The floor of polished jet-black stone reflects the cool light of
the magical flames in dim, pale blue pools. A passageway leads off into the
darkness, flanked at the entrance by two imposing black marble statues.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 73 ADJ1=348 ADJ2=218 ADJ3=312 VAL2=3371 
; wide obsidian stone passage (leading into Subterranean Garden)
ITEM 1 346 ADJ1=317 ADJ2=87 ADJ3=312
; tall dark stone statue
ITEM 9 693
; ucantsee
EXTEND 1 of an armored Mardhrel warrior
ITEM 2 72 ADJ1=209 ADJ2=658 ADJ3=150 VAL2=640
; mysterious silvery gray opening (out to Shartans, ledge by crevice to Deep Realms)
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The passage itself is unlit, but the dim glow of magelight from either end
provides sufficient illumination.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 1
Clad in full plate armor and a visored helm, the figure could be either male
or female. It stands with feet firmly planted, hands resting on the hilt of
the drawn sword planted point-downward before it.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 2
Whatever is on the other side of the opening is blurred by a rippling, semi-
translucent barrier, almost as though viewed through swiftly running water.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO 0
  IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
    IFVAR RAC = 2
      IFVAR ALIGN < 5
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You turn and stride down the passage, under the watchful eyes of the guardians.
        ECHO OTHERS %N turns and strides down the passage, under the watchful eyes of the guardians.
        DISBAND
        MOVE 3371
        AFFECT 3371
        ECHO OTHERS %P arrives from the passage leading to the entry hall.
        AFFECT 3370
      ELSE
        DAMAGEPLR SLASH 100 The statues guarding the passage animate and slash at you with their weapons!
        ECHO OTHERS The guardian statues animate and slash at %N with their weapons!
        POSITION LAY
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
