CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
A flat gray plain stretches out in every direction as far as the eye can
see, meeting the looming, overcast sky at an impossibly distant horizon.
A dim, sourceless light illuminates the entire space in a silvery-gray
twilight, bright enough to see by yet casting no shadows. There seem to 
be no walls, but somehow one can never go more than a few dozen paces from
the small deep pool of the shrine, no matter how long one walks.
